9 not as a result of works, that no one should boast.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cendan and all, I am a non-denominational Christian. What the above quotation from Paul the Apostle means to me is that God's grace saves us period, no questions.<br>
<br>
Human's are dead in sin by nature. Because of a sinful nature we can't see the need for salvation. Only divine intervention can help us see we need help from God.<br>
<br>
Cendan, I can't say whether or not you are saved, but reading your responses to Tuan, Lurikeen, Brutas, and Lith makes me wonder if you have really experienced the full grace of my Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. If you had, then I wonder were you got the ideas that you can save yourself by following a baptismal prescription? I once met a United Pentecostal who told me I had to not only repent of my sins, but be baptised with precisely the words &quot;in the name of Jesus&quot; invoked over me and then I had to speak in tongues to prove I had the baptism of the Holy Spirit. If I didn't follow that &quot;prescription&quot; I was sure to roast with Satan for an eternity.<br>
<br>
Cendan, you seem to be saying many of the same things. So let me ask you this Brother: where does God give you the authority to question the grace of Christ? Please quote chapter and verse. It is by Grace we are saved through faith! Not by any act of repentance, baptism, talking in tongues. The evidence of salvation is in the heart, and ONLY GOD knows the hearts of men and women. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucendan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cendan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 552<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/13/02 2:42:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=220>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: Expectations and consequences of God</span><hr size=1> Curran,<br>
<br>
We are saved through grace, the Bible says so.  There is no question to that.<br>
<br>
Okay, I don't know what makes this so hard, its right in the Bible, but I am going to point it out in hopes that you will go look it up.  Don't believe me... just go look.<br>
<br>
<font color=yellow>I wonder were you got the ideas that you can save yourself by following a baptismal prescription? </font color><br>
<br>
I have been very clear, very clear, that I have not saved myself, nor have I done anything to deserve salvation.  Baptism only saves you in the sense that it is the POINT at which you recieve salvation which is made possible by the death, burial, and resurrection of Christ.  It is the point that you appeal to God and you confess Him as Lord, and a desire to accept Him as Lord.<br>
<br>
The United Pentecostal was obviously wrong, so what does that have to do with me or with the Gospel?  We have to confess Christ as our savior for sure, but where does it even say that you must speak that out loud?  In the Name of Jesus, is a given and need not be spoken.  As far as the speaking in tongues... I would simply show him several baptisms in scripture where that did not happen.<br>
<br>
Now, you question whether I am saved and then later call me brother, not sure which you believe but if you have not been baptised for the remission of your sins then I know whether you are my brother or not.<br>
<br>
You can't pick out a verse on faith and say "look we are saved by faith."  If you do that then I can pull out 1peter 3:21 and say "look, baptism now saves you."  Doing that, however, you say that one verse negates the other.  That is not the case.  It is both.  Baptism is not a how, its a when.<br>
  <br>
Now, as to me quetioning the grace of Christ.. show me where.  I do not question the grace, the grace is a free gift OFFERED to all.  Lets compare it to a blank check.  If I give you a blank check its free right?  Have you earned it? No.  So, you go to the bank and you tell them... I want 1 billion dollars (sorry, have to warnyou here that it would bounce).  They are still going to ask you to sign the back.  Do you earn it by signing the back? NO.<br>
<br>
Now I know that isn't a perfect example but I don't know how to make it any more clear.<br>
  <br>
<font color=yellow>It is by Grace we are saved through faith! Not by any act of repentance, baptism, talking in tongues. The evidence of salvation is in the heart, and ONLY GOD knows the hearts of men and women.</font color><br>
<br>
So, if we are not saved at the point of baptism then when are we saved, please include chapter and verse, with biblical example.  After the cross of course.<br>
<br>
Let me also point out that 1 Peter 3:21 says that baptism IS an appeal to God for a clean conscience, through the ressurection of Jesus Christ. Can you please explain what that means in light of your theory of salvation.<br>
<br>
