No Cendan it is not correct. Your are commiting a fallacy. You are isolating a particular phrase and then interpreting. The fallacy is called isogesis. Here read, Acts 10:47-48 &quot;Surely no one can refuse the water for these to be baptized who have received the Holy Spirit just as we did, can he?&quot; And he ordered them to be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ.&quot; What does that passage mean Cendan? If one has already recieved the Holy Spirit they are a child of God! Again, you must take into context what the Apostles taught, what Jesus taught. You can't just isolate phrases and then draw out doctrine.<br>
<br>
<br>
